      • doSlide

        public boolean doSlide​(Pawn p,
                       Deck b,
                       int i)
        Check is the pawn lands on a StartSlideSquare if it lands on StartSlideSquare then moves to EndSlideSquare else it stays on the square. Also if the StartSlideSquare is of same color then it stays on the square.
        Parameters:
        p - Pawn
        b - Deck
        i - The square the pawn landed
        Returns:
        true if it slided else returns false
        Postcondition
        If the pawn moved to the end of the slide or it stayed in the same square if there was not a StartSlideSquare
